WEBVTT

00:04.070 --> 00:07.139
      (slow solemn music)       

00:22.490 --> 00:25.724
     (school bell ringing)      

00:36.637 --> 00:40.172
      - [Voiceover] I           
      believe in control,       

00:40.174 --> 00:42.341
     the only force mighty      
     enough to bring order      

00:42.343 --> 00:44.710
 in the chaos that is my world. 

01:03.364 --> 01:05.129
          - Congrats!           

01:05.132 --> 01:06.832
         - Oh, thanks.          

01:06.834 --> 01:09.601
      - "Oh thanks." Like       
      it's not a big deal?      

01:09.603 --> 01:11.703
       - It's really not.       

01:11.705 --> 01:13.772
    - To some people, it is.    

01:38.466 --> 01:39.465
          - Hey Lyla.           

01:40.568 --> 01:41.533
       Sorry about the--        

01:41.535 --> 01:42.801
         - Oh, please.          

01:42.803 --> 01:45.404
       I'd much rather          
       be your VP anyway.       

01:45.406 --> 01:46.505
            - Okay.             

01:46.507 --> 01:50.309
     Alright ladies, settle     
     down, settle down.         

01:50.311 --> 01:53.245
  Alright, see we're all here.  

01:53.247 --> 01:57.249
   Oh, I had a chance to read   
   these and I have to say,     

01:57.251 --> 01:59.685
these are really, really great. 

02:00.788 --> 02:04.490
     Thought-provoking and      
     critically engaging.       

02:04.492 --> 02:08.193
   I am very, very              
   impressed with your work.    

02:11.198 --> 02:15.767
  Now, anyone who's interested  
  in a little extra credit      

02:15.769 --> 02:18.137
     should consider            
     applying to Columbia's     

02:18.139 --> 02:20.506
 annual Young Writer's Program. 

02:21.876 --> 02:26.311
They're accepting applicants    
for their pre-college workshop. 

02:29.717 --> 02:32.718
 I think you'd be a great fit.  

02:32.720 --> 02:34.153
           Yes, Lyla.           

02:34.155 --> 02:35.354
     - If we apply, can we      
     come by after school       

02:35.356 --> 02:36.922
for some extra one-on-one help? 

02:36.924 --> 02:40.259
        (girls giggling)        

02:40.261 --> 02:41.160
             - Um,              

02:42.329 --> 02:43.462
      you can use the rest      
      of the class time         

02:43.464 --> 02:45.264
   to work on the assignment.   

02:45.266 --> 02:48.800
   If you have any questions,   
   feel free to ask.            

02:50.538 --> 02:52.571
     - I got a freaking B+,     
     can you believe it?        

02:52.573 --> 02:54.373
       - You did so bad.        

02:54.375 --> 02:55.474
   - Well, what did you get?    

02:55.476 --> 02:56.441
             - Um,              

02:57.344 --> 02:58.443
           I passed.            

02:58.445 --> 03:02.281
      - He said he wasn't       
      gonna be easy on us.      

03:02.283 --> 03:05.484
       - Well, you got          
       an A, didn't you?        

03:05.486 --> 03:07.419
      - Of course she did.      

03:08.589 --> 03:11.523
        (hip-hop music)         

03:12.760 --> 03:15.494
   - [Boy In Car] Hey Belle!    

03:15.496 --> 03:16.562
          - Oh my God.          

03:17.565 --> 03:20.399
- [Boy In Car] Look what I got. 

03:23.437 --> 03:24.670
          Want a ride?          

03:24.672 --> 03:25.737
     - [Girl With Ponytail]     
     You have to say yes.       

03:25.739 --> 03:26.638
           - Say no.            

03:37.885 --> 03:38.784
           - Hi guys.           

03:39.553 --> 03:41.320
       Hey Gus, nice car.       

03:41.322 --> 03:42.821
    - [Gus] Come on, get in.    

03:42.823 --> 03:44.323
           - No way.            

03:44.325 --> 03:45.557
        - Well, why not?        

03:45.559 --> 03:48.393
      (car engine revving)      

03:48.395 --> 03:50.362
Look, I'll just drive you home. 

03:50.364 --> 03:52.397
- Gus, you don't have a license.

03:52.399 --> 03:53.498
         [Gus Scoffing]         

03:53.500 --> 03:54.566
         - Yeah, I do.          

03:54.568 --> 03:56.268
        - No, you don't.        

03:56.270 --> 03:57.636
   You have a permit, you're    
   supposed to be driving       

03:57.638 --> 03:58.971
         with a parent.         

03:58.973 --> 04:00.272
       - Yeah, well yeah        
       yeah, whatever.          

04:00.274 --> 04:01.873
     Just come on, get in.      

04:08.582 --> 04:09.481
            - Sorry.            

04:22.496 --> 04:24.496
      Then, Mr. Davy said       
      I had a good chance       

04:24.498 --> 04:26.431
at getting into the program, so 

04:26.433 --> 04:28.033
I'm gonna apply for the summer. 

04:28.035 --> 04:29.668
     - [Belle's Dad]            
     Well, that's perfect.      

04:29.670 --> 04:33.005
 - Which means I have to go     
 to Columbia for the workshop,  

04:33.007 --> 04:34.673
     which means I already      
     have a good chance         

04:34.675 --> 04:37.609
at getting in there for college.

04:37.611 --> 04:40.479
   I know it's early, but       
   you have to start thinking   

04:40.481 --> 04:43.982
  about college early, because  
  one thing affects another     

04:43.984 --> 04:45.717
      and everything else.      

04:47.921 --> 04:48.820
             - Hmm.             

04:52.293 --> 04:55.427
- Why don't you ever ask me     
how my day at school goes, dad? 

04:55.429 --> 04:59.765
   - We know we don't have      
   to worry about you, Belle.   

04:59.767 --> 05:01.433
- I got elected class president.

05:01.435 --> 05:04.303
 - [Belle's Dad] That's great,  
 sweetie, congratulations.      

05:04.305 --> 05:05.003
           - Thanks.            

05:09.476 --> 05:11.443
- President of the school, wow. 

05:11.445 --> 05:13.378
      My baby is so smart.      

05:13.380 --> 05:15.447
      - Not of the school,      
      dad, just my class.       

05:15.449 --> 05:16.915
    Like the freshman class.    

05:16.917 --> 05:19.017
        (phone buzzing)         

05:19.019 --> 05:19.985
     - [Belle's Dad] Sorry.     

05:19.987 --> 05:20.886
           Yeah, Bob.           

05:27.828 --> 05:32.064
  - [Voiceover Of Belle] Name:  
  Annabelle. Grade: freshman.   

05:33.334 --> 05:36.902
     Class: English Honors.     
     Teacher: Mr. Davy.         

05:41.408 --> 05:42.441
         My role model...       

05:45.412 --> 05:49.381
   My role model is my mom      
   because she is the person    

05:49.383 --> 05:52.351
      in my life who            
      cares most about me.      

05:53.921 --> 05:57.489
    She is smart, beautiful,    
    and hard-working,           

06:00.361 --> 06:02.060
     everything I wanna be.     

06:04.064 --> 06:05.731
       She helped me make       
       pins and posters         

06:05.733 --> 06:07.766
 for my presidential campaign,  

06:07.768 --> 06:11.370
   helped me write my speech,   
   and even baked cupcakes      

06:11.372 --> 06:12.437
          for the PTA.          

06:17.444 --> 06:19.378
     She wants to see me        
     succeed and pushes me      

06:19.380 --> 06:22.114
to live up to my full potential.

06:22.916 --> 06:24.983
    I try to make her proud.    

06:36.096 --> 06:38.830
        (ominous music)         

07:45.766 --> 07:47.933
   - Mom, mom can I come in?    

07:51.705 --> 07:53.538
      Mom! I'm coming in!       

07:56.043 --> 07:56.975
              Mom.              

08:04.485 --> 08:05.984
       Dad, where's mom?        

08:08.856 --> 08:10.589
     - Uh, in the darkroom.     

08:10.591 --> 08:14.092
       - No she's not, I        
       was just in there.       

08:14.094 --> 08:15.026
    - I don't know, sweetie.    

08:15.028 --> 08:16.561
   She must have stepped out.   

08:16.563 --> 08:18.763
       - All her photos,        
       everything's gone.       

08:18.765 --> 08:21.666
   - You know, she must have    
   had an exhibition tonight.   

08:21.668 --> 08:24.236
 - She didn't tell me about it. 

08:37.251 --> 08:38.149
              Mom.              

08:46.827 --> 08:49.261
  Hey mom, it's your Anabelle.  

08:49.263 --> 08:51.730
     Just wanna know when       
     you were coming home.      

08:51.732 --> 08:54.599
     I got some really good     
     news at school today.      

08:54.601 --> 08:57.736
Call me back when you get this. 

08:57.738 --> 09:01.306
     Oh! I'm applying for       
     this writer's program      

09:02.676 --> 09:05.277
  and I've been working on my   
  application essay all day.    

09:05.279 --> 09:09.314
 I should really take a break,  
 but I kinda wanna finish it.   

09:11.585 --> 09:13.752
   Are you at an exhibition?    

09:15.255 --> 09:16.721
       I can come visit.        

09:18.158 --> 09:20.825
Call me back when you get this. 

09:32.072 --> 09:34.839
   Mom, I didn't get to tell    
   you about the PTA meeting.   

09:34.841 --> 09:37.309
    It's Friday at seven and    
    I'm gonna give my speech    

09:37.311 --> 09:39.144
      as class president.       

09:40.314 --> 09:43.582
  Oh, that's my good news, I    
  got elected class president.  

09:43.584 --> 09:48.053
   So if you get home early,    
   maybe we can go to dinner    

09:48.055 --> 09:50.288
   or something to celebrate.   

09:51.325 --> 09:54.159
   I mean, it's not president   
   of the school, but           

09:54.161 --> 09:56.161
    it's still good, right?     

10:00.634 --> 10:02.267
      Mom, where are you?       

10:22.689 --> 10:24.789
     - Everything alright?      

10:24.791 --> 10:25.690
            - Fine.             

10:32.332 --> 10:34.232
     - You can take a break     
     every once in a while.     

10:34.234 --> 10:35.934
       - That's alright.        

10:39.773 --> 10:41.673
    - Belle, if you ever        
    need someone to talk to,    

10:41.675 --> 10:43.975
    well, you know where I      
    am, so you can always--     

10:43.977 --> 10:46.111
     - I'm good, Mr. Davy.      

10:46.113 --> 10:47.012
            Thanks.             

11:09.302 --> 11:10.368
          Is mom home?          

11:16.076 --> 11:17.242
    Have you talked to her?     

11:17.244 --> 11:19.277
     - Yeah, this morning.      

11:19.279 --> 11:23.281
    - Really? Why hasn't she    
    been answering my calls?    

11:23.283 --> 11:25.383
     - She just needs time.     

11:27.187 --> 11:28.019
          - For what?           

11:28.021 --> 11:29.254
         - For herself.         

11:30.257 --> 11:32.390
  Belle, you know how she is.   

11:39.733 --> 11:41.966
           (sighing)            

12:12.466 --> 12:15.400
        (ominous music)         

13:12.325 --> 13:14.492
    - So, are you guys doing    
    a theme for the dance?      

13:14.494 --> 13:16.194
     - Belle and I haven't      
     really discussed it.       

13:16.196 --> 13:18.864
   We'll probably talk about    
   it at the next meeting.      

13:18.865 --> 13:21.533
  - A fire-hot freshman theme,  
  kinda like an inferno!        

13:21.535 --> 13:23.368
   - Are you going with Gus?    

13:23.370 --> 13:24.335
        - To the dance?         

13:24.337 --> 13:25.904
       - No, to the moon.       

13:27.440 --> 13:31.242
   - She doesn't even wanna     
   go with him anyway, right?   

13:31.244 --> 13:33.211
       - Yeah, of course.       

13:33.213 --> 13:35.647
        - I don't know.         

13:35.648 --> 13:38.082
 In some sort of weird way,     
 they're kind of cute together. 

13:38.084 --> 13:39.284
   - You're too good for him.   

13:39.286 --> 13:40.919
     There's so many other      
     cute Briary boys.          

13:40.921 --> 13:42.153
- That your parents won't hate. 

13:42.155 --> 13:44.122
     - Oh yeah, what's up       
     with your mom anyway?      

13:44.124 --> 13:46.891
     Heard she hasn't been      
     home in like a week.       

13:46.893 --> 13:47.525
    - Where'd you hear that?    

13:47.527 --> 13:48.860
         - Small town.          

13:49.996 --> 13:53.031
       - Yeah well, she's       
       away on business.        

13:54.901 --> 13:56.401
       - Photographers          
       do business trips?       

13:56.403 --> 13:58.369
- [Blonde Girl] Where'd she go? 

13:58.371 --> 14:00.171
    - Anybody want the rest?    

14:00.173 --> 14:01.973
     I had a big breakfast.     

14:01.975 --> 14:03.274
        - I'll take it.         

14:07.314 --> 14:10.915
        (girls chatting)        

14:10.917 --> 14:12.217
          - Hey Belle.          

14:12.219 --> 14:13.551
           - Hey Gus.           

14:13.553 --> 14:14.886
- [Gus] What's going on, Belle? 

14:14.888 --> 14:16.221
      - Nothing much, Gus.      

14:16.223 --> 14:17.322
      - [Gus] Want a ride?      

14:17.324 --> 14:18.623
       - Not today, Gus.        

14:55.462 --> 14:58.930
    (computer alert beeping)    

15:25.325 --> 15:28.259
        (ominous music)         

15:48.682 --> 15:51.449
    - [Mr. Davy] Next on        
    the agenda, committees.     

15:51.451 --> 15:53.284
    Now, we're looking for      
    parents who have not yet    

15:53.286 --> 15:56.521
   signed up for a committee    
   to help with fundraising.    

15:56.523 --> 15:58.489
  - Is your mom still heading   
  publicity this year?          

15:58.491 --> 16:00.124
   - [Belle] Yes, of course.    

16:00.126 --> 16:03.161
      - When is she coming      
      back from her trip?       

16:03.163 --> 16:04.395
        - I'm not sure.         

16:04.397 --> 16:05.997
       - [Lyla] Haven't         
       you talked to her?       

16:05.999 --> 16:06.698
             - Yes.             

16:08.101 --> 16:10.785
       I left a message.        

16:10.786 --> 16:13.470
  - A message, so you haven't   
  actually spoken to her?       

16:15.508 --> 16:18.142
    She didn't really leave     
    for work, did she?          

16:18.144 --> 16:19.210
          - Excuse me.          

16:21.214 --> 16:22.447
    - [Mr. Davy] And now,       
    I'd like to turn it over    

16:22.449 --> 16:24.182
      to our headmaster...      

16:27.487 --> 16:28.753
    - [Headmaster] Welcome      
    to the first PTA meeting    

16:28.755 --> 16:30.121
       of freshman year.        

16:30.123 --> 16:32.457
           (applause)           

16:48.375 --> 16:49.424
        - Where's Belle?        

16:49.425 --> 16:50.474
       - I think she went       
       to the bathroom.         

16:50.477 --> 16:51.376
             - Now?             

17:05.492 --> 17:07.157
      - Hey, uh, nervous?       

17:08.461 --> 17:09.460
          - I'm good.           

17:11.664 --> 17:14.699
      - Yeah, you are, but      
      do you know that?         

17:14.701 --> 17:16.233
          - Know what?          

17:16.236 --> 17:17.468
         - You're good.         

17:19.105 --> 17:20.570
   Okay, (mumbles)              
   - I gotta make my speech.    

17:20.573 --> 17:22.540
      - Look, how about         
      we get out of here?       

17:22.541 --> 17:25.042
  How about I drive you home?   

17:28.615 --> 17:30.248
       Look, you know you       
       don't have to do         

17:30.250 --> 17:33.151
       anything you don't       
       want to, right?          

17:40.794 --> 17:44.629
     - Now, I'll turn it        
     over to our executive      

17:44.631 --> 17:47.365
 board freshman class president 

17:47.367 --> 17:49.467
       who will give a          
       couple of remarks        

17:49.469 --> 17:54.272
discussing some of the upcoming 
events this year, so...         

17:54.274 --> 17:56.474
           (applause)           

18:00.613 --> 18:01.846
     - Thanks, I got this.      

18:06.252 --> 18:07.518
       Thanks, Mr. Davy.        

18:09.322 --> 18:11.456
    Firstly, I just want to     
    thank all the parents       

18:11.458 --> 18:13.558
      in attendance today       
      who are so engaged        

18:13.560 --> 18:16.327
 in their children's education. 

18:20.400 --> 18:21.232
     - [Voiceover Of Belle]     
     I want to believe          

18:21.234 --> 18:22.500
     my mom is coming back.     

18:22.502 --> 18:26.637
    I mean, it's not like       
    she's done this before,     

18:26.639 --> 18:30.141
      but for some reason,      
      I'm not surprised.        

18:33.613 --> 18:36.414
     No matter how involved     
     in my life she was,        

18:36.416 --> 18:38.883
she's always seemed distracted, 

18:41.354 --> 18:45.590
  not really listening, there,  
  but not like really there.    

18:51.831 --> 18:53.698
    Well, she was there for     
    everyone else to see,       

18:53.700 --> 18:56.400
 but come to think of it, I...  

18:58.838 --> 19:02.673
    I don't remember the        
    last time she hugged me.    

20:13.713 --> 20:16.414
  - [Lyla] What are you doing?  

20:16.416 --> 20:18.549
       - [Belle] Nothing.       

20:18.551 --> 20:20.551
     - Your dad let me in.      

20:24.891 --> 20:25.723
           New hobby?           

20:25.725 --> 20:27.391
        - It's my mom's.        

20:27.393 --> 20:30.361
  - [Lyla] She won't get mad?   

20:30.363 --> 20:31.629
 - No, she said I could use it. 

20:31.631 --> 20:32.964
      - You talked to her?      

20:32.966 --> 20:36.968
     - Yeah, she just gotta     
     figure some stuff out.     

20:36.970 --> 20:37.868
            - Right.            

20:41.541 --> 20:44.542
 - Um, so do you wanna do       
 just traditional pink and red  

20:44.544 --> 20:46.310
       or red and black?        

20:46.312 --> 20:47.812
   I was actually thinking we   
   could do something classy.   

20:47.814 --> 20:51.282
   Maybe black and white        
   with pink and red accents,   

20:51.284 --> 20:55.753
 but Olivia's so set on red-hot 
 theme, that I don't know.      

20:55.755 --> 20:56.754
            - Right.            
            - Yeah.             

20:56.756 --> 20:57.989
  I found this great website.   

20:57.991 --> 21:00.658
      Here, I'll show you       
      some of my ideas.         

21:02.462 --> 21:04.662
  - [Lyla] Who is this person?  

21:05.932 --> 21:07.531
         - [Belle] Who?         

21:07.533 --> 21:09.667
  - This person, right there.   

21:14.440 --> 21:17.008
  - I don't know who that is.   

21:17.010 --> 21:18.809
- But why are you on this page? 

21:18.811 --> 21:20.645
     - I mean, it's just--      

21:21.781 --> 21:24.882
       - Why does it say        
       your name is Ana?        

21:24.884 --> 21:26.484
- Nobody uses their real names. 

21:26.486 --> 21:27.785
         - So you lie?          

21:27.787 --> 21:30.054
     - Well, Ana is the         
     first part of my name,     

21:30.056 --> 21:31.689
      so technically, no.       

21:32.592 --> 21:33.491
             - Wow.             

21:35.695 --> 21:37.595
     - It's not a big deal.     

21:39.332 --> 21:40.031
     - You're not planning      
     on killing yourself        

21:40.033 --> 21:41.465
      or anything, right?       

21:41.467 --> 21:42.366
          - What? No.           

21:42.368 --> 21:43.618
    Why would you say that?     

21:43.619 --> 21:44.869
     - I don't know, it         
     just looks like that.      

21:44.871 --> 21:46.937
    - No, it's just thinspo.    

21:48.541 --> 21:50.041
            - Right.            

21:50.043 --> 21:53.077
   - Thinspiration, just        
   inspiration to keep thin.    

21:53.079 --> 21:55.446
   - I know what thinspo is.    

22:00.853 --> 22:02.586
      - Don't tell anyone?      

22:05.792 --> 22:06.691
          - Of course.          

22:10.697 --> 22:13.464
 - [Mr. Davy] How does the 25th 

22:15.101 --> 22:17.001
         work for you?          

22:17.003 --> 22:19.370
   We should set up a meeting   
   of the executive council.    

22:19.372 --> 22:20.371
       I was thinking we        
       could get started        

22:20.373 --> 22:22.340
 on the dance early this year.  

22:22.342 --> 22:24.575
    It is our big fundraiser    
    for the spring trip,        

22:24.577 --> 22:27.078
and I was wondering if your mom 

22:27.080 --> 22:28.412
could give us some of the photos

22:28.414 --> 22:30.514
       that she has from        
       last year's dance        

22:30.516 --> 22:31.716
 to help them with his year's.  

22:31.718 --> 22:33.884
      I didn't see her          
      at the PTA meeting.       

22:33.886 --> 22:35.619
      - Oh, she was there.      

22:35.621 --> 22:36.821
           - She was?           

22:36.823 --> 22:37.722
             - Mhm.             

22:40.360 --> 22:42.493
         You know what?         

22:42.494 --> 22:44.627
   I'll tell her to bring it    
   to back-to-school night.     

22:44.630 --> 22:45.963
        - Sounds great.         

22:48.968 --> 22:51.469
     - So how are you gonna     
     pull that one off?         

22:51.471 --> 22:53.104
      - What do you mean?       

22:54.006 --> 22:56.774
- You're only lying to yourself.

23:06.552 --> 23:09.453
       (energetic music)        

23:17.463 --> 23:19.130
      - [Belle] Let's go.       

23:19.132 --> 23:20.998
      - Uh, are you sure?       

23:21.000 --> 23:21.832
     (school bell ringing)      

23:21.834 --> 23:22.833
          - Hurry up.           

23:28.508 --> 23:32.143
      (car engine revving)      

23:32.145 --> 23:33.577
- [Girl On Left] That is Belle. 

23:33.579 --> 23:34.612
     - [Girl With Gray Bag]     
     That can't be Belle.       

23:34.614 --> 23:36.714
